Package msoe.swe2721.lab2

Class CircularQueue<E>

java.lang.Object
msoe.swe2721.lab2.CircularQueue<E>
Type Parameters:
E - This is the object type that is to be stored on the queue.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Queue<E>, FixedSizeQueueInterface<E>
public class CircularQueue<E> extends Object implements FixedSizeQueueInterface<E>
This class will implement a circular queue. The user can use this class to store items in an efficient manner.

    • CircularQueue

      public CircularQueue(int maxQueueSize) throws IllegalArgumentException
      This constructor will instantiate a new circular queue of the size given as an attribute.
      Parameters:
      maxQueueSize - This is the capacity of the circular queue. It must be greater than 0.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - An IllegalArgumentException will be thrown if an invalid capacity is passed into the method. The capacity must be greater than zero for a proper queue structure to be built.
